13 further amended to read:
14 D. If the candidate has an opponent who is on the ballot or who is a declared write-in
15 candidate, any single contribution of $1,000 $10,000 or more received or any single
16 expenditure of $1,000 $10,000 or more made after the 14th day before the election and
17 more than 24 48 hours before 11:59 p.m. on the day of the election must be reported
18 within 24 48 hours of that contribution or expenditure. The candidate or treasurer is
19 not required to include in this report expenditures for overhead expenses or
20 compensation paid to an employee or other member of the campaign staff who has
21 received payments at regular intervals that have been disclosed in previously filed
22 campaign finance reports. As used in this paragraph, "overhead expenses" includes,
23 but is not limited to, rent, utility payments, taxes, insurance premiums or similar
